item.title: CVE-2023-0429|2023-02-21T08:50:57.365Z -- unknown -- watu%20quiz
item.description: The Watu Quiz WordPress plugin before 3.3.8.2 does not sanitise and escape some of its settings, which could allow high privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example in multisite setup).

item.title: CVE-2023-0428|2023-02-21T08:50:56.586Z -- unknown -- watu%20quiz
item.description: The Watu Quiz WordPress plugin before 3.3.8.2 does not sanitise and escape a parameter before outputting it back in the page, leading to a Reflected Cross-Site Scripting which could be used against high privilege users such as admin.
